╭─ assistant [MainThread@1705412] ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────╮
│ THOUGHT: My infinite loop detection fix is breaking many tests because it's too broad - it's disabling horizontal reduction for loops that do have exit          │
│ conditions but might have self-loops as one of their successors.                                                                                                 │
│                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ The issue is that `successors(InsertPt->getParent())` includes all successors, and if any successor is the same block, it doesn't mean it's an infinite loop.    │
│ Many valid loops have the loop header as a successor.                                                                                                            │
